    "abstractNote": "An attempt is made in this article to throw some light on the circumstances in which Bar Ebroyo (Barhebraeus) worked by focusing our attention on the priest-physician Simeon b. Joshua of Qalca Rumaita (ob. 1289), who rose to a position of some importance at the Ilkhanid court in the 1260's and whose nephew Nemrod became patriarch under the name of Philoxenus in 1283. The fact that two of Bar Ebroyo's works are dedicated to this Simeon suggests that he may have played an important role in the background to Bar Ebroyo's literary activity.",
